==Translingual==
{{CJKV-forms|難|难|難|難}}

===Alternative forms===
* In {{w|traditional Chinese}}, Japanese {{w|kyūjitai}}, Korean {{w|hanja}} and Vietnamese [[Nôm]], the component [[File:U26c29-ue0102.svg|25px|text-bottom|𦰩󠄂|link=𦰩]] for this character is written with {{l|mul|廿}} on top. Note that the bottom portion is written {{l|mul|口}} overlapped by {{l|mul|夫}} and not {{l|mul|中}} on top of {{l|mul|天}}.
* In Japanese {{w|shinjitai}}, the component [[File:U26c29.svg|25px|text-bottom|𦰩|link=𦰩]] is written with <span style="font-size:x-large;", lang=ja>[[艹#Translingual|艹]]</span> on top and has one stroke less. Due to {{w|Han unification}}, both traditional Chinese and Japanese forms are encoded under the same [[code point]]. The appearance of this character will differ according to the font used.
* In {{w|simplified Chinese}}, the component [[File:U26c29-ue0102.svg|25px|text-bottom|𦰩󠄂|link=𦰩]] is simplified to {{l|mul|又}} instead, giving the character <big>{{l|mul|难}}</big> (<code>U+96BE</code>).
* Two {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs|compatibility ideographs}} exist for this character. <code>U+FA68</code> corresponds to the {{w|kyūjitai}} form of this character while <code>U+FAC7</code> corresponds to the alternative Korean form which is similar to Japanese shinjitai.

